##Direct Fire Mountain Hospital: the first batch of patients have been admitted to the hospital, the scene busy assembly end

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. "CAIJING" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was first published in 1998, adhering to the news concept of "independence, exclusiveness and originality" , and is known for authoritative, impartial and professional reporting, it is a must-read publication for policy-makers, researchers and managers in the field of politics and economics.

The following article is from 11 people in Finance and Economics, author Liu Yiqin, Han Shulin

The Wuhan Huoshenshan Hospital, which was born in response to the epidemic, has the fastest construction speed and the most scientific and technological equipment in history. On the morning of February 4, the first part of the ward opened officially received the first batch of patients. CAIJING reporter on the afternoon of February 3 to see at the scene, responsible for the completion of thousands of staff still maintain high-intensity work to complete the final equipment assembly

Wen | Caijing reporter Liu Yiqin, Wuhan Caijing reporter Han Shulin, Beijing

Editor | Sheryl Rong

February 2, the rare speed of the completion of the Wuhan Huoshenshan Hospital held a grand completion and delivery ceremony. Some 1,400 military medical personnel are scheduled to begin treatment on Feb. 3. CAIJING reporter learned that February 3 at about 8:00 pm, the Fire Mountain hospital part of the early completion of Medical Equipment Assembly Ward, ready to receive the operation of the patients. At about 9:20 a.m. on Feb. 4, an ambulance convoy arrived at the Vulcan Mountain Hospital, where the first group of patients had already been admitted. About 50 patients have been admitted to the hospital so far, CCTV reported.

At 2:00 p.m. on February 3, caijing reporters rushed to the Huoshenshan Hospital in Caidian District, Wuhan, and saw that part of the site was still in the final stage of equipment installation after completion and delivery, with air conditioning and ventilation equipment being installed one after another, a number of suction machines, beds and other medical equipment placed in the road leading to Mount Vulcan. However, in some wards of the hospital, "finance" reporter saw that some beds are ready, some installed ventilation, insulation, moisture and other equipment has begun to run.

A construction worker at the site told Caijing that in the morning he saw an ambulance come in, but quickly turned back under armed police escort. CAIJING reporter saw two ambulances at the scene. There were no medical staff or patients on board.

"We can't send patients in yet, " a construction manager told Caijing, adding that he expected it would take another two to three days for the hospital to be fully equipped and operational. It is reported that the nearby Raytheon Mountain Hospital due to the construction start time is slightly late, should be more than the Fire Mountain Hospital a few days to complete the equipment assembly and officially opened.

Around 4 p.m. on Feb. 3, the manager heard that a patient might arrive that day. As of 6 p.m. , CAIJING reporters at the scene had yet to see a patient arrive. However, the reporter of "Caijing" saw many medical staff and armed police in the hospital, preparing for the admission and treatment of patients. A medical staff told Caijing that she did not know when to start treating patients.

Two hours later, on February 3 at around 8 pm, Caijing reporter learned that the first batch of patients began to transfer from the designated hospitals to the Huoshenshan Hospital. The Wuhan Emergency Center sent 10 ambulances to take part in the transfer operation. Vulcan Mountain hospital part of the first completion of Medical Equipment Assembly Ward, can receive and treat the operation of patients, which means that the hospital officially opened.

At 10 pm, the scene of the Fire Mountain Hospital tense atmosphere, thousands of staff on the scene to speed up the finishing work, some staff began to do the final preparation before the opening of the ward, such as sweeping the road stairs, cleaning ward, etc. . Field staff were informed that the first batch will be transferred into dozens of patients, patients admitted, they will continue to complete the final assembly work. As of 11:20 p.m. on Feb. 3, the first batch of patients had not yet been admitted. The patient is on his way, according to the CCTV-13.

CAIJING reporter learned on the spot that on the night of February 3, the ambulance returned 10 minutes away from the fire God mountain. As the ward was not ready, it was adjusted to the day of February 4 to start receiving patients. According to the CCTV report, the first batch of patients have been admitted to the hospital around 9:20 am on February 4. Currently, 50 patients are being treated in the Huoshenshan Hospital.

From January 24, the design of Huoshenshan hospital was completed, to February 2, the completion of delivery, February 4 began to treat patients, Wuhan Huoshenshan hospital has created a number of new records.

A project engineer from Huawei's Huoshenshan hospital told Caijing that if the previous construction speed was walking, the urgent task was running, "Then this is the speed of the rocket. " This is behind a large number of workers working day and night, as well as the result of technological progress.

Of the Vulcan Hills Hospital

The Vulcan Mountain Hospital is located in Caidian District, Wuhan, near the Bosom Friend Lake. Following the model of Beijing's Xiaotangshan Hospital during the 2003 SARS outbreak, the hospital has built a special hospital in the Wuhan Workers'sanatorium to focus on patients with COVID-19 pneumonia. The hospital has a total Gross leasable area of 33,900 square meters and 1,000 beds. It has set up intensive care units, critical care units and general ward units, as well as auxiliary departments for infection control, examination, special diagnosis and radiation diagnosis.

According to public information released by the China Construction and Construction Bureau, the ground with a maximum height difference of nearly 10 meters between the east and the west of the construction site should be levelled before full construction. Existing buildings need to be demolished, as well as a large number of dredging and fishpond backfilling tasks. However, the whole project is built on the water, there is only one main road around to the site, material traffic in and out of the pressure is huge, gas, high-pressure relocation coordination volume.

The China Construction Bureau sent 4,000 workers, in addition to many workers from other construction companies and local residents to participate in the construction. "CAIJING" reporters see, left at the scene to finish the assembly of the staff still maintain high-intensity work, a site management personnel revealed that there are still thousands of workers at the construction site.

The worker is now working two 12-hour shifts, with fewer breaks for the manager, who has taken an average of two hours off each day since New Year's Eve, the official said. The CAIJING reporter noticed that his eyes were red and his voice was hoarse and he could hardly speak.

Huawei, Lenovo, Xinhua and other technology equipment manufacturers are involved in the construction of the Fire Mountain Hospital. Huawei has sent more than 100 staff to work with operators to help set up network equipment on site. Lenovo sent 15 employees to bring 500 computers and 275 printers to the hospital.

The Huawei Engineer said the biggest difficulty they had was staffing. When the fire God mountain started, Wuhan had already closed the city, and the towns around Wuhan also had road closures of varying degrees. Some colleagues in their rural hometowns could not even leave the village. To complete the project on time, Huawei must have sufficient manpower. Through the coordination of all parties, Huawei finally realized the arrival of personnel, but it was not enough either, "All of us are working as a couple, we have very little time to rest and the workers have food to go with it, so we have to make do with what we have. "

Lenovo donated 500 computers and 275 printers to Vulcan Mountain Hospital. A project director involved in the reconstruction assistance told Caijing that most of the local staff in Wuhan had already gone home in the run-up to the Spring Festival. It was indeed difficult to find temporary staff. In addition, it would have been easy to install computers and printers, but there are many practical difficulties in an environment as tight as Vulcan Mountain and incomplete network environment.

The above Lenovo Project Director revealed that the entire Vulcan Mountain Hospital Information Construction Wechat group has more than 40, every minute has a large amount of wechat information gushing, because it involves a large number of collaborative work, so they dare not miss a message.

As of 21:00 on February 3,11,177 cases had been confirmed, 295 cases had been cured and 2,103 new cases had been reported in Hubei Province, according to the real-time epidemic report. In Wuhan, 5,142 people have been diagnosed, 228 have been cured and 265 have died. According to the Wuhan Health Commission, Wuhan's designated hospitals had 7,259 beds open as of 23:00 on February 2, of which 7,332 had been used and 131 were vacant.

The number of confirmed cases in Wuhan is still on the rise, and the difficulty of hospitalizing a large number of suspected patients is becoming more and more prominent. A doctor at a designated front-line hospital told the CAIJING reporter that the opening of the Vulcan Mountain and Raytheon Mountain hospitals can effectively ease the pressure on hospitals in the urban areas, and patients with severe diagnoses can be immediately transferred to hospitals, "We can open up beds for other patients. "

It is reported that the fire God mountain and the Thunder God mountain hospital altogether altogether has 2,600 beds. But according to public figures, Hubei Province added 2,103 confirmed cases on February 2, of which 1,033 were in Wuhan. There are concerns about whether the two hospitals will be enough. A doctor at a designated hospital told Caijing that at present, the number of patients who are seriously ill is not very large, most of them are still patients with mild illness, can be isolated at home, or the community unified arrangements for isolation.

Behind the Vulcan Mountain speed

Compared with Xiaotangshan during the SARS period in 2003, the construction of the Vulcan Mountain and Raytheon Mountain Hospital, a major bright spot is the use of new technology.

For most ordinary people, the first time to see the Vulcan Mountain, is through the CCTV live broadcast, in the Vulcan Mountain scene, deployed a number of cameras, real-time recording the construction site. The Vulcan Mountain Hospital on-site communication and network equipment, by a number of technology manufacturers to participate in the construction.

On the morning of Feb. 3, a front-line employee of Huawei told Caijing that they have installed new spherical cameras and VR devices, so people can watch the progress of the two mountains at 360 degrees on their mobile phones, he said, medical supplies will be arriving in large numbers at the two hospitals soon, and all sectors of society are closely monitoring and monitoring the distribution of supplies. VR technology can help meet this need.

Compared with Xiaotangshan Hospital 17 years ago, the modular, can be like building blocks as "Patchwork" box-style room greatly accelerated the construction of the Fire Mountain Hospital, so that "10 days to build a hospital" become possible.

Huoshenshan hospital not only adopts modern construction technology, but also uses a lot of high-tech in construction and operation, including 5G, cloud computing and so on. The time limit for the construction of Huoshenshan hospital is 10 days, but in fact it is only 4-5 days. Cloud computing technology accelerates the whole construction cycle significantly.

For example, the core information systems of HIS and PACS in Huoshenshan hospital were deployed based on the Chinese Telecom's skywing cloud. Because of the cloud-based deployment, China Telecom completed the information system construction in only 12 hours, the traditional model takes at least 10 days. The Lenovo executive also said that because of the use of smart cloud desktop technology, only 24 hours to install and debug nearly 800 devices.

5g technology can also be used for intelligent telemedicine and teleconsultation. For patients, time is life, Wuhan local medical resources are limited, the local medical staff also need to stay. The technology has the direct effect of reducing exposure, allowing patients to be treated as quickly as possible, and allowing severe cases to be seen by multiple specialists as quickly as possible, especially during large outbreaks of infectious disease.

In the 4G era, telemedicine has already been realized, but the advantage of 5G is that it can keep the network running smoothly when doctors consult with each other. Huawei engineers say they no longer care about the cost-effectiveness of the technology, only whether they can treat patients, to the best of my ability.

On the peripheral equipment, new technology is everywhere. Respiratory disease is so demanding for air purification that wards at Vulcan and Raytheon hospitals are equipped with a negative pressure system to vent dirty air through special pipes.

Due to the high demand for air quality and the need for air-conditioning equipment to avoid pollution, Midea and gree each donated 1,000 and 1,605 air-conditioning units in the construction of the Vulcan and Raytheon Mountains, the relevant officials of the two companies told CAIJING, the donated air-conditioners are all new air-conditioners equipped with new technology, which can effectively discharge dirty air and avoid air pollution.

CEO  Zhang Tao, the founder of purdue technology, told Caijing that the company has also docked with Mount Vulcan and Mount Thor, and plans to offer medical delivery robots, with 50 each expected to be used.

ULAMBANA's robots can provide touch-free food delivery in hospitals and quarantines, reducing the risk of infection. The introduction of the product manual shows that the self-developed SLAM (Simultaneous localization and mapping) technology can realize the functions of centimeter real-time localization, high-precision map construction, optimal path planning and instantaneous intelligent obstacle avoidance, in addition, a self-developed distributed scheduling system is applied to multi-computer cooperation. The robot's battery can be recharged in four hours, and it can run continuously by changing the power supply.

The location of Huoshenshan hospital is close to Zhiyin Lake, and Wuhan is rich in groundwater system. Whether the construction of temporary hospital will cause pollution is a problem that many Wuhan residents are concerned about.

A wuhan-based design institute with design experience in the field of environmental protection has analyzed CAIJING. In designing a hospital, rain and sewage diversion should be considered: first, medical waste water should be sterilized by a complete set of equipment, and then enter the urban sewage system, it ends up in the Sewage Treatment; the other part is Leachate, like rainwater that carries germs away from hospitals, and leachate that can be produced during the transportation of medical waste.

Typically, the first type of wastewater is collected centrally by a hospital, enters a front end wastewater treatment facility, is discharged through a physical grid and biochemical treatment to meet standards, and is discharged to a nearby Sewage Treatment for treatment. However, the risk of the latter kind of seepage liquid needs to be well treated, and it is generally necessary to lay a impervious membrane in the construction process to prevent the seepage and pollution of surface water to the ground, so as to avoid the pollution of nearby water body and groundwater.

People involved in the project of the China Construction and third bureau told the CAIJING reporter that the waste water from the hospital will be treated and discharged into the municipal pipe network. In terms of anti-seepage, first, two layers of anti-seepage membranes are laid under the pipe, second, the project is located under the board room are covered with anti-seepage membrane. The source also said that CCB 3 had already had rich experience in the construction of hospital projects. Famous hospitals in Wuhan, such as Hankou Tongji Hospital, Guanggu Tongji Hospital and Wuhan Asian Heart Hospital, were all constructed by CCB 3, therefore familiar with the relevant construction standards.

According to a report on January 26 on the Chu website of the Hubei Daily, the Huoshenshan hospital laid two layers of Geomembrane, two layers of geotextile and one layer of HDPE membrane, and then laid 20 cm of sand, it has a strong anti-seepage effect. In the wastewater treatment, by the construction of the Third Green Investment Company to organize relevant experts design, wastewater after three-stage liquid chlorine disinfection pumping municipal pipe network. The whole base under the standard landfill site laid anti-seepage Membrane, rainwater collection full disinfection.

At 7:30 pm on February 2, after the handover ceremony, Huawei Engineers from Wuhan left the site and returned to the city to rest. He told his wife that it was time to watch the live VR broadcast of Vulcan Mountain. "This is what we do for the people of Wuhan, " he said. The construction workers will leave as soon as they are finished, but the technicians will have a much bigger job to keep the equipment running throughout the hospital.

(also contributed by CAIJING reporter Zhou Yuan)
